spec: as3181
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(asyncio)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/asyncio.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/asyncio.html"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source code"
    - "any proprietary source"
  notes:
    - "Wave 659 (as3181): __truediv__, __floordiv__, __mod__ dict-presence for asyncio types."
    - "All values verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13."
    - "Classes covered: asyncio.Task, asyncio.Future, asyncio.Queue, asyncio.Event, asyncio.Semaphore, asyncio.Lock, asyncio.Condition, asyncio.BoundedSemaphore, asyncio.Handle, asyncio.TimerHandle, asyncio.Timeout, asyncio.TaskGroup, asyncio.StreamReader, asyncio.StreamWriter."
    - "Key finding (__truediv__): all 14 asyncio classes return false for __truediv__. The / operator (true division) is a numeric protocol with no relevance to concurrency primitives. asyncio.Queue does not define queue / n; asyncio.Semaphore does not define semaphore / n. asyncio.StreamReader/StreamWriter manage byte-stream I/O via read()/write() — division has no meaning for stream objects. asyncio.Handle/TimerHandle manage callback scheduling; true division of a callback handle is undefined."
    - "Key finding (__floordiv__): all 14 asyncio classes return false for __floordiv__. The // operator (floor division) is not defined for any asyncio type. asyncio.Queue, asyncio.Semaphore, asyncio.Lock, asyncio.Condition, asyncio.BoundedSemaphore, asyncio.Event: synchronization primitives with no arithmetic semantics. asyncio.Timeout/TaskGroup: async context managers with no division protocol. asyncio.Task/Future: coroutine wrappers whose results are retrieved via result() — not computed via //."
    - "Key finding (__mod__): all 14 asyncio classes return false for __mod__. The % operator (modulo/remainder) is not defined for any asyncio type. No asyncio concurrency primitive has a modulo operation: asyncio.Queue does not define queue % n; asyncio.Semaphore does not define semaphore % n. asyncio.TimerHandle manages deadline offsets but does not expose % for time arithmetic. asyncio.StreamReader/StreamWriter: byte streams with no modulo protocol."
    - "This is the sixth consecutive all-false wave for all 14 asyncio subjects (waves 654–658 were also all-false for the same subjects). The asyncio library defines no arithmetic operators whatsoever — its API is built entirely on async/await, context-manager protocols, and explicit method calls."
    - "Cross-wave summary for asyncio subjects:"
    - "  Wave 652 (as3076): __get__ — Task/Future/Queue/Handle true; others false."
    - "  Wave 653 (as3091): __hash__/__eq__/__bool__ — selected true."
    - "  Wave 654 (as3106): __lt__/__le__/__gt__ — TimerHandle true; others false."
    - "  Wave 655 (as3121): __ge__ — TimerHandle true; __repr__ — 12 classes true."
    - "  Wave 656 (as3136): __call__/__len__/__getitem__ — all false for all 14."
    - "  Wave 657 (as3151): __setitem__/__delitem__/__contains__ — all false for all 14."
    - "  Wave 658 (as3166): __add__/__sub__/__mul__ — all false for all 14."
    - "  Wave 659 (as3181): __truediv__/__floordiv__/__mod__ — all false for all 14."
  created_at: "2026-04-13"

error_model: python_exceptions

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# __truediv__ dict-presence — operator.contains(Cls.__dict__, '__truediv__')
#
# All 14 asyncio classes return false for __truediv__.
# asyncio types are concurrency primitives, not numeric types.
# asyncio.Task/Future: coroutine result containers; task / task is undefined.
# asyncio.Queue: FIFO queue managed via put()/get(); no division protocol.
# asyncio.Semaphore/Lock/Condition/BoundedSemaphore: synchronization guards
#   tracking permits or exclusive access; none define true division.
# asyncio.Handle/TimerHandle: callback schedule objects; no division.
# asyncio.Timeout/TaskGroup: async context managers; no arithmetic.
# asyncio.StreamReader/StreamWriter: byte-stream I/O; no division.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

