# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# __mod__ dict-presence — operator.contains(Cls.__dict__, '__mod__')
#
# All 14 asyncio classes return false for __mod__.
# No asyncio type defines modulo or remainder.
# asyncio.Semaphore tracks a counter with acquire()/release() — the count
#   does not participate in modulo arithmetic via %.
# asyncio.TimerHandle stores a deadline (float seconds) but does not expose
#   % for time arithmetic; time math is handled by the event loop internals.
# asyncio.Queue: queue % n is undefined. Queue capacity is set at construction
#   (maxsize); it does not wrap around via modulo.
# asyncio.Task/Future/Handle/Condition/Lock/BoundedSemaphore/Event:
#   no modulo semantics of any kind.
# asyncio.Timeout/TaskGroup/StreamReader/StreamWriter: async utility objects
#   with no remainder or formatting protocol.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

