# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# combined — __truediv__, __floordiv__, __mod__ across all 14 asyncio subjects
#
# Covers the full matrix: 14 classes x 3 methods = 42 rows.
# __truediv__: false for all 14 — true division (/) not defined for any asyncio type.
# __floordiv__: false for all 14 — floor division (//) not defined.
# __mod__: false for all 14 — modulo (%) not defined.
# All 42 values are false.
# This is the sixth consecutive all-false wave (654–659) for all 14 subjects.
# The asyncio library has now returned false for every single arithmetic dunder
# tested across waves 652–659: __get__ (partial true), __hash__/__eq__/__bool__
# (partial true), __lt__/__le__/__gt__/__ge__ (partial true), __repr__ (partial
# true), then a pure all-false run from wave 656 onward through __call__, __len__,
# __getitem__, __setitem__, __delitem__, __contains__, __add__, __sub__, __mul__,
# and now __truediv__, __floordiv__, __mod__.
# asyncio is a pure concurrency API — its classes interact through async/await
# and explicit method calls only. No arithmetic data model is implemented.
# Cross-wave summary for asyncio subjects:
#   Wave 652 (as3076): __get__ — Task/Future/Queue/Handle true; others false.
#   Wave 653 (as3091): __hash__/__eq__/__bool__ — selected true.
#   Wave 654 (as3106): __lt__/__le__/__gt__ — TimerHandle true; others false.
#   Wave 655 (as3121): __ge__ — TimerHandle true; __repr__ — 12 classes true.
#   Wave 656 (as3136): __call__/__len__/__getitem__ — all false for all 14.
#   Wave 657 (as3151): __setitem__/__delitem__/__contains__ — all false for all 14.
#   Wave 658 (as3166): __add__/__sub__/__mul__ — all false for all 14.
#   Wave 659 (as3181): __truediv__/__floordiv__/__mod__ — all false for all 14.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

